headline: Does New US$3 Billion Credit Line And Strong Orders Change The Bull Case For TE Connectivity (TEL)?
summary: In recent days, TE Connectivity plc entered into a US$3.00 billion five-year senior revolving credit facility with Bank of America, alongside reporting a strong first-quarter order book above US$5.00 billion and guiding to second-quarter adjusted profit above consensus expectations. This combination of enhanced liquidity and solid demand linked to industrial automation, automotive electronics, and AI-related infrastructure highlights how TE Connectivity is positioning itself as a key...
